<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently we can pass to the Zend_Queue_Adapter_Db only array with connection options.
I have tried to use SQLite to store queue's messages, could not do it, bacause I could not set <em>host _, _username</em>  and <em>password</em> options (these options do not necessary for SQLite).</p>

<p>It will be easier to work with Zend_Queue_Adapter_Db if we can pass $db object directly instean of options array.</p>

<p>Here is sample code:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$db = Zend_Db::factory($options['type'], $options);

$queue = new Zend_Queue('Db', $db);
</code></pre>

